# 🛡️ OWASP Juice Shop - Security Assessment Report

## 📋 Project Overview

| **Field** | **Details** |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Application Tested** | OWASP Juice Shop (Deliberately Vulnerable Web Application) |
| **Assessment Type** | Security Vulnerability Assessment & Penetration Testing |
| **Tester Name** | Alisha Ayaz |
| **Assessment Date** | 24 April, 2026 |
| **Tools Used** | OWASP ZAP, Browser DevTools, cURL, Nmap |

---

## 🎯 Objective

To identify, analyze, and document security vulnerabilities in an e-commerce product review system and provide actionable recommendations for remediation.

---

## 🚀 Application Setup

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/juice-shop/juice-shop.git

# Navigate to project directory
cd juice-shop

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start the application
npm start

# Access the application
http://localhost:3000
________________________________________
🔍 Vulnerability Assessment Summary
#	Vulnerability	Risk Level	Status
1	Cookie Without SameSite Attribute	🟡 Low	Found
2	CSP Header Not Set	🟡 Low	Found
3	X-Content-Type-Options Missing	🟡 Low	Found
4	X-Frame-Options Not Set	🟡 Low	Found
5	Suspicious Developer Comments	🟡 Low	Found
6	Server Version Information Leak	🟡 Low	Found
7	No Rate Limiting on Reviews	🟠 Medium	Found
8	Unsanitized User Reviews (Stored XSS)	🟠 Medium	Found
________________________________________
📊 Detailed Findings
1. Cookie Without SameSite Attribute
•	Risk Level: 🟡 Low
•	Description: Session cookies missing SameSite attribute, vulnerable to CSRF attacks
•	Location: Product review submission endpoint
2. Content Security Policy (CSP) Header Not Set
•	Risk Level: 🟡 Low
•	Description: Missing CSP allows any script to execute regardless of origin
•	Location: All HTML response pages
3. X-Content-Type-Options Header Missing
•	Risk Level: 🟡 Low
•	Description: Missing nosniff header creates XSS opportunities
•	Location: Static asset delivery
4. X-Frame-Options Header Not Set
•	Risk Level: 🟡 Low
•	Description: Application vulnerable to clickjacking attacks
•	Location: Entire application
5. Information Disclosure - Suspicious Comments
•	Risk Level: 🟡 Low
•	Description: Developer comments expose internal logic
•	Location: Product review page, Admin panel
6. Server Leaks Version Information
•	Risk Level: 🟡 Low
•	Description: X-Powered-By header reveals Express.js version
•	Location: All HTTP responses
7. No Rate Limiting on Review Submission
•	Risk Level: 🟠 Medium
•	Description: Unlimited review submissions allowed
•	Location: /api/submit-review endpoint
8. User Reviews Not Sanitized Before Display
•	Risk Level: 🟠 Medium
•	Description: Stored XSS via unsanitized review content
•	Location: Product review display section
________________________________________
🛠️ Tools Used
Tool	Purpose
OWASP ZAP 2.14	Automated vulnerability scanning
Browser DevTools	Manual XSS testing, header inspection
cURL	HTTP response header analysis
Nmap	Port and service enumeration
________________________________________
📝 Testing Methodology
Test Case	Test Input	Result
Stored XSS in Review	<img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>	❌ VULNERABLE
Rate Limiting Test	100 reviews in 10 seconds	❌ VULNERABLE
Cookie Security Check	Inspect browser storage	❌ VULNERABLE
CSP Validation	Check response headers	❌ VULNERABLE
Frame Embedding	Load site in iframe	❌ VULNERABLE
________________________________________
✅ Areas of Improvement (Priority Wise)
🔴 High Priority (Immediate)
#	Recommendation	Expected Outcome
1	Sanitize all review inputs before display	Prevent stored XSS attacks
2	Implement rate limiting on review submissions	Block spam and DoS attempts
🟡 Medium Priority (Next Sprint)
#	Recommendation	Expected Outcome
3	Add SameSite attribute to cookies	Prevent CSRF attacks
4	Implement CSP headers	Reduce XSS and injection threats
5	Add review moderation queue	Block malicious content
6	Add CSRF tokens to forms	Prevent cross-site request forgery
🟢 Low Priority (Future)
#	Recommendation	Expected Outcome
7	Remove suspicious developer comments	Prevent information leakage
8	Disable server version headers	Reduce attack surface
9	Add security.txt file	Provide security contact
10	Implement Subresource Integrity	Ensure CDN asset integrity
________________________________________
